# **LEARNING MARKDOWN**
## What is Markdown
markdown is a **lightweight markup language** with a palin text formatting syntax.
It is easy to use and easy to understand . Github has it's own version of markdown syntax which provide additional features to it.
we are going to study how to format things in markdown.
### what we are going to learn:
1. how to use headers or make headings
    * make letters bold and italic

1. how to use images in ur document
1. how to add links.
1. make tables and task lists.


`let's get started`

--how to add haedings:

`#` is used for haedings and u can use `##` for sub headings.
therefore u can use `#` upto `#######` to denote ur headings

**example**

if u type `# this is heading one` and `## this is heading 2` then ur result is:
# this is heading one
## this is heading 2

--how to make words bold and italic

It is very easy to make words `**bold**` and `*italic*` .

It is very easy to make words **bold** and *italic*

u can also use __bold__ for bold and _italic_ for italic.

--how to create tables

tables are created by separating each row by hyphens (--) and each coulmn by pipe(|)

**for example**

student | teacher
--------|--------
this is first coulmn|this is 2nd coulmn
jyoti|priyanka saggu

--how to use links and images

to create a link :
syntax = [text](url)

**for exampe**

[github](https://github.com/)

[markdown](https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/#examples)

to use image:
 
 syntax=![text](url)

**for example**
![github logo](https://github.githubassets.com/images/modules/logos_page/Octocat.png)

click here to get the best way to learn markdown 
[tutorial for learning markdown](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUBNt18RFbo&t=74s)

--how to add task list:

- [x] task1
- [x] task2
- [ ] task3

U can also use emojis ,github has a sepearte cheat sheet for emojis which contain all types of emojis in it.
 
and here the link for that cheat sheet
[emojis](https://github.com/ikatyang/emoji-cheat-sheet/blob/master/README.md "emoji cheat sheet")

This is a small discription about what markdown is and how u can use it.There are many markdown editors like vscode,atom,vim etc,u can use any of them to format ur document.

